In[66]:
X = Data['Age']
Y = Data['Height']

beta_0 = 164.6385 #(Inercept)
beta_1 = 0.0937 #(Slope)

y_pred = beta_0 + beta_1*X

sns.scatterplot(x = X, y=Y)
plt.title('Age Vs. Height')

plt.plot(X, y_pred, color = 'red', label = 'Trendline')

plt.legend()

plt.xlabel('Age')
plt.ylabel('Height')
plt.show()

this predicts that there could be an increase in height as age increases

-Multiple linear Regression: $$Y= \beta_0 + \beta_1X_1 + \beta_2X_2 + \dots + \beta_nX_n + \epsilon$$
